It's time to head to Sol City to challenge the first Antares League gym! The way to Sol City is north, along Kraken Bridge , a grassy wetland that cuts through the giant lake, Ligeia Mare.
When you arrive, head over to the gym. A queue has formed and blocks your way. The recent Trainer's School graduates will move if you ask them... after a battle!

Whether or not you want to battle him, make your way through the western part of Sol City to find Pytheas so you can get a PokeNav. On the bridge, there's a trainer battle in progress. Team Nova is back!

The defeated trainer happens to be Pytheas! Very convenient. He'll accompany you for a while to pick up some skills, and he'll give you a PokeNav when you get to his house.
He'll take you to Sol City Cavern , and suggest a quick detour to the depths of the inner cavern.

After realizing that exploring this cavern is sort of a bad idea, it's time to head to Pytheas' house.
With Pokenav in hand, let's see if the gym is clear for a challenge. On your way over, it's a good idea to head west to Versant Megrez and meet Rarai, a friendly illusionist who likes inverse battles. She'll accept you as a rival and give or teach you something useful each time you battle her.
